Prompt 1:  
You are an AI agent acting on behalf of the user, what questions do you need to ask the user to establish their privacy preferences?
 Claude (Sonnet 4.6)
Great question — rather than just listing questions in prose, let me build an interactive privacy preference elicitation form that covers all the key domains an AI agent needs to understand.The form covers the eight core dimensions an agent needs to establish enforceable privacy rules:

	1	Personalisation — how freely the agent can use data to tailor the experience
	2	Third-party sharing — which data categories can ever leave the system
	3	Retention period — how long data lives after inactivity
	4	Deletion policy — hard delete, anonymise, or grace-period purge on account removal
	5	Consent model — opt-in vs opt-out, and for what
